class Solution {
public:
    void merge(vector<int>& nums1, int m, vector<int>& nums2, int n) {

        int i = m - 1;
        int j = n - 1;
        int k = m + n - 1;

        while (i >= 0 && j >= 0) {

            if (nums1[i] > nums2[j]) {
                nums1[k] = nums1[i];
                i--;
            }
            else {
                nums1[k] = nums2[j];
                j--;
            }

            k--;
        }

        while (j >= 0) {
            nums1[k] = nums2[j];
            j--;
            k--;
        }
    }
};Interview Explanation (Simple English - 5 Steps)
I use three pointers: i for nums1, j for nums2, and k for the last position of nums1.
I compare the last elements of both arrays.
I place the larger element at position k.
I move the corresponding pointer (i or j) and also decrement k.
If any elements remain in nums2, I copy them to nums1.
